MIOpen's serializable helper includes ciso646 solely for the alternative
operator tokens. Those tokens are built into C++, and ciso646 was removed from
the standard in C++20. GCC 15 consequently diagnoses the include, which becomes
a build failure under MIOpen's -Werror.

--- a/rocm-libraries/projects/miopen/src/include/miopen/serializable.hpp
+++ b/rocm-libraries/projects/miopen/src/include/miopen/serializable.hpp
@@ -27,7 +27,6 @@
 #ifndef GUARD_MLOPEN_SERIALIZABLE_HPP
 #define GUARD_MLOPEN_SERIALIZABLE_HPP
 
-#include <ciso646>
 #include <miopen/config.h>
 #include <iostream>
 #include <sstream>
